info.headline: Flood Warning issued June 05 at 9:34AM EDT until June 06 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Melbourne
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida... St Johns River Near Astor affecting Volusia and Lake Counties. .Increased northeast winds and high astronomical tides have caused the St Johns River at Astor to reach Minor Flood Stage. River levels are forecast to hover around or potentially just above Minor Flood Stage through early this week, before falling back to Action Stage by mid-week. For the St. Johns River...including Astor...Minor flooding is forecast. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued this evening at 1100 PM EDT. && ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL TOMORROW EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...St Johns River Near Astor. * WHEN...Until tomorrow evening. * IMPACTS...At 2.3 feet, Minor flooding of low lying streets and yards north of Fox Road on Lake County side of Astor, and from River Road northward on Volusia side of river. Water begins to cover docks at South Moon Fish Camp. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 8:30 AM EDT Monday the stage was 2.3 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 2.3 feet this afternoon. It will then fall below flood stage tomorrow evening. - Flood stage is 2.3 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood && Fld Observed Forecasts (8 am) Location Stg Stg Day/Time Tue Wed Thu Fri Sat St Johns River Astor 2.3 2.3 Mon 8 am 2.3 2.2 2.0 1.7 1.6 &&
